The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Unique venue!
                                                                                                                       7                                      Unique venue!
                      
	Schwechat: Austria will play France on a clay court in an aircraft hangar in the first round of the 2011 Davis Cup.         
	The Austrian tennis federation announced Wednesday that a 10,000 square meter hangar at Austrias main airport  20 kilometers east of Vienna  will be transformed into a 6,000-capacity tennis stadium for the March 4-6 tie.         
	(Jurgen Melzers manager) Ronnie Leitgeb came up with the idea... Its a unique project, federation vice-president Helmut Dorn said.         
	Austria have not got past the first round of the Davis Cup since 1995. Nine-time champions France lost the 2010 final 3-2 to Serbia.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
